=== Etymology ===
From Latin ''gaudium'' meaning "joy" via French.

== [[adjective]] ==
#(''old-fashioned'') happy, joyful and lively.
#(''old-fashioned'') bright and colorful.
#homosexual.
#used by or intended for homosexuals.
#typical of homosexual appearance or behavior. 
#''Slang''. boring, unappealing, bad or of low quality.


== [[noun]] ==
#a homosexual, most often a male homosexual but sometimes applied to female homosexuals

